GateDocument.TextWithNodes: CALL FOR PAPERS Fourth International Workshop on Multimedia Information Systems ( MIS'98 ) September 24 - 26 , 1998 Istanbul , Turkey MIS Workshop Series sponsor : U . S . Army Research Office MIS'98 Cosponsors : University of Maryland Institute for Advanced Computer Studies Center for Secure Information Systems , George Mason University Research Institute for Multimedia Systems , University of Alberta Middle East Technical University , Ankara , Turkey Bosphorus University , Istanbul , Turkey The Fourth Workshop on Multimedia Information Systems ( MIS'98 ) , the fourth version of a series of workshops which started in 1995 with the aim of fostering interdisciplinary discussions and research in all aspects of multimedia information systems , will be held in Istanbul , Turkey , from September 24 to 26 , 1998 . This workshop follows upon the success of the three workshops in this series that were held in Arlington , VA , West Point , NY , and Como , Italy . As in the past , this is a small focused workshop , consisting of participants drawn from a wide variety of disciplines ( e . g . theory , algorithms , real-time systems , networks , operating systems , graphics and visualization , databases , artificial intelligence , etc . ) , all of whom are engaged in research on one or more aspects of multimedia systems . Authors are invited to submit six copies of their papers ( maximum 4000 words ) or one-page description of the panel to the following address by May 1 , 1998 . Manuscripts must be in English , typed in double spaced format in 12 point font , and not more than 5000 words . Each copy should have a cover page with name , title , and address ( including e-mail address ) of authors , and an abstract of no more than 200 words . Electronic or fax submissions of papers will not be accepted . Postal Address : Prof . Sushil Jajodia Mail Stop 4 A 4 George Mason University Fairfax , VA 22030 - 4444 Address for Express Delivery : Prof . Sushil Jajodia Room 330 , Science and Technology II Bldg . George Mason University Fairfax , VA 22030 - 4444 Phone : ( 703 ) 993 - 1653 Fax : ( 703 ) 993 - 1638 Internet : jajodia @ cns . kpjx . ydttnw Selection will be based on originality and contribution to the field . The proceedings will be published as one of the volumes in the Springer Lecture Notes in Computer Science Series and will be available at the workshop . Panel Proposals : Proposals for panels should also be sent to program chair . Proposals should include a one-page description of the subject matter , the name and address ( including e-mail address ) of the organizer , and a list of proposed panelists . Electronic submissions are preferred .
